Privacy Policy
Effective Date: December 3, 2024

At Devious Devs, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our games, websites, and related services ("Services").

By using our Services, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:

1.1. Information You Provide to Us
Contact information, such as your email address, when you sign up for newsletters or support.
Payment information when you make in-app purchases (processed through third-party platforms).
User-generated content, such as feedback, gameplay data, or submissions.
1.2. Information We Collect Automatically
Device information, such as your device type, operating system, and unique identifiers.
Usage data, including gameplay statistics, in-app interactions, and preferences.
Log data, such as IP addresses, crash reports, and timestamps.
1.3. Information from Third Parties
We may receive information from third-party services, such as app stores or social media platforms, if you interact with our Services through these channels.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:

Provide, maintain, and improve our Services.
Process payments and in-app purchases.
Communicate with you, including responding to inquiries and sending updates or promotional offers.
Personalize your experience, including in-game recommendations and tailored content.
Monitor and analyze usage trends to improve our Services.
Ensure the security and functionality of our Services.
3. Sharing Your Information
We do not sell your personal information. We may share it in the following limited circumstances:

With Service Providers: Third-party partners who assist in payment processing, analytics, hosting, or support services.
For Legal Compliance: When required by law or to protect the rights and safety of our users or others.
Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred to the new entity.
4. Your Privacy Choices
4.1. Access and Update Your Information
You may request access to or correction of your personal data by contacting us at pandazflipperpanda706@gmail.com.

4.2. Opt-Out of Communications
You can opt out of marketing communications by following the unsubscribe instructions in our emails.

4.3. Do Not Track Signals
Our Services do not currently respond to "Do Not Track" signals.

4.4. Data Deletion Requests
You can request the deletion of your data by contacting us. Note that some data may need to be retained for legal or operational reasons.

5. Security
We implement industry-standard measures to protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Third-Party Services
Our Services may contain links to third-party websites or use third-party services (e.g., payment processors, analytics). We are not responsible for their privacy practices, and we encourage you to review their policies.

7. International Data Transfers
If you use our Services outside [Insert Your Country], your information may be transferred to and processed in [Your Country], where data protection laws may differ.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Significant changes will be communicated through our Services or other appropriate channels. The updated policy will take effect upon posting.

